frameDefinitions: In this frame, an Agent changes the temperature of an Item.
In this frame, the temperature of an Item changes.
In this frame a Patient undergoes a change of phase.
An Entity changes from a Prior_state to a Post_state in a sequence that follows a pre-defined plan, expectation, or model of change.
The Temperature in a certain environment, determined by Time and Place, is specified.
frameExamples: Margaret Anne <t>chilled</t> the salad to 30 degrees.
The house had <t>cooled</t> <t>off</t> by a few more degrees by midnight, and we finally managed to eat a bite.
Their offensive armament has <t>developed</t> from short range missiles to long-range ballistic weaponry in a relatively short period .
It's too <t>hot</t> to do anything today.
listRoleDefinitions: The <fen>Agent</fen> performs the intentional act which changes the temperature of the <fen>Item</fen>.
The <fen>Item</fen> undergoes the temperature change.
An animate or inanimate entity, a force, or event that changes the temperature. Volitionality is not a necessary characteristic of <fen>Cause</fen>s.
The <fen>Hot_Cold_source</fen> is the source of the heat or coolness.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when  the <fen>Agent</fen> changes the temperature of the <fen>Item</fen>.
This role identifies the <fen>Place</fen> where  the <fen>Agent</fen> changes the temperature of the <fen>Item</fen>.
The entity whose temperature changes.
The scalar property that the <fen>Item</fen> possesses.  This role is rarely expressed.
The time at which the change in temperature occurs.
The location at which the <fen>Item</fen> changes temperature.
<fen>Patient</fen> is the entity that undergoes a change of phase.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> at which the <fen>Patient</fen> changes phase.
Where the <fen>Patient</fen> changes phase.
The object that undergoes change.
The time at which the progress occurs.
The location where the Progress occurs.
The <fen>Place</fen> where  it is a certain <fen>Temperature</fen> .
The temperature feature of the weather.
A quantity or other characterization of the <fen>Temperature</fen> of the environment.
A modifier expressing  the deviation of the <fen>Temperature</fen> from the norm.
The <fen>Time</fen> during which an ambient environment has a particular <fen>Temperature</fen>.
The meteorological conditions which determine the ambient temperature of a locale.
listRoleExamples: <fex>Ryan</fex> reheated the pasta in the microwave.
Ryan reheated <fex>the pasta</fex> in the microwave.
The raw fish that is to be eaten as sushi has to be meticulously prepared and must first be chilled <fex>in temperature</fex> to exactly above freezing point.
Advances <fex>in marketing techniques</fex> have since rendered it obsolete.
<fex>When</fex> did the X-wing progress beyond the drawing board?
The temperature  was <fex>85 F</fex> in the shade today
It's like <fex>totally</fex> chilly, dude, like, totally.
We get warmer <fex>weather</fex> this time of year.
